{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17511013","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17511013"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T12:36:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T12:36:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11671"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583543","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583543"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:18:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:18:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11671"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"11671","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/11671"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.68,0.06,0.01,0.24]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4292"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43436"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4292","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4292"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11671"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28417"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"40"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"2078"},{"type":"tags","id":"2765"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"7861"},{"type":"tags","id":"10962"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"5788"},{"type":"contributions","id":"5937"},{"type":"contributions","id":"11186"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43436","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/43436"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 77-year old woman presents to the Emergency Department with sudden onset central crushing chest pain, radiating down the left arm. She is cold, clammy and has increased work of breathing. Her ECG show ST elevation in leads II, III and aVF.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most specific marker in this clinical presentation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Creatinine Kinase-MM","Troponin I","Creatinine Kinase-MB","Lactate Dehydrogenase","Troponin T"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient is suffering from an acute myocardial infarction (STEMI). Troponin is a cardiac-specific marker that is found exclusively in the myocardium. Ischaemia leads to myocardium necrosis, and as the myocytes break down leakage of these proteins occurs, and  becomes detectable in the blood.\u003Cstrong\u003E Cardiac troponin I (cTnI) \u003C/strong\u003Eis typically more elevated than \u003Cstrong\u003Ecardiac troponin T (cTnT)\u003C/strong\u003E in an acute myocardial infarction, whereas cTnT is often higher in patients with stable conditions such as atrial fibrillation. \u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECreatinine Kinase-MM \u003C/strong\u003Eis found in high concentrations in muscle tissue and thus is not a cardiac-specific biomarker. \u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECreatinine Kinase-MB\u003C/strong\u003E is found in both heart and skeletal muscle. Its specificity and sensitivity for myocardial infarction are lower compared with troponins. \u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELactate Dehydrogenase \u003C/strong\u003Ecatalyses the final glycolysis step by converting pyruvate to lactate. It is found in nearly every tissue of the body. Thus, it is not specific or sensitive to myocardial infarction. \u003Cbr /\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Troponin I is highly specific and sensitive in diagnosing acute myocardial infarction."],"references":["Saenger AK, Jaffe AS. Requiem for a heavyweight: the demise of creatine kinase-MB. Circulation 2008; 118:2200.","Jaffe AS, Lindahl B, Giannitsis E, et al. ESC Study Group on Cardiac Biomarkers of the Association for Acute CardioVascular Care: A fond farewell at the retirement of CKMB. Eur Heart J 2021; 42:2260.","Rose BD, Post TW. Clinical Physiology of Acid-Base and Electrolyte Disorders, 5th ed, McGraw-Hill, New York 2001. p.583","Espinosa AS, Hussain S, Al-Awar A, Jha S, Elmahdy A, Kalani M, Kakei Y, Zulfaj E, Aune E, Poller A, Bobbio E, Thoirleifsson S, Zeijlon R, Gudmundursson T, Wernbom M, Lindahl B, Polte CL, Omerovic E, Hammarsten O, Redfors B. Differences between cardiac troponin I vs. T according to the duration of myocardial ischaemia. Eur Heart J Acute Cardiovasc Care. 2023 Jun 2;12(6):355-363. doi: 10.1093/ehjacc/zuad017. PMID: 36848390."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28417"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"11671"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"28417","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/28417"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-03-17T19:59:40+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-03-17T19:59:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4292"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"43436"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","